    • Constructor Detail

      • RamseteAutoBuilder

        public RamseteAutoBuilder​(Supplier<Pose2d> poseSupplier,
                          Consumer<Pose2d> resetPose,
                          RamseteController controller,
                          DifferentialDriveKinematics kinematics,
                          SimpleMotorFeedforward feedforward,
                          Supplier<DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds> speedsSupplier,
                          PIDConstants driveConstants,
                          BiConsumer<Double,​Double> outputVolts,
                          Map<String,​Command> eventMap,
                          Subsystem... driveRequirements)
        Create an auto builder that will create command groups that will handle path following and triggering events.

        This auto builder will use PPRamseteCommand to follow paths.

        Parameters:
        poseSupplier - A function that supplies the robot pose - use one of the odometry classes to provide this.
        resetPose - A consumer that accepts a Pose2d to reset robot odometry. This will typically be called once at the beginning of an auto.
        controller - The RAMSETE controller used to follow the trajectory.
        kinematics - The kinematics for the robot drivetrain.
        feedforward - The feedforward to use for the drive.
        speedsSupplier - A function that supplies the speeds of the left and right sides of the robot drive.
        driveConstants - PIDConstants for each side of the drive train
        outputVolts - Output consumer that accepts left and right voltages
        eventMap - Map of event marker names to the commands that should run when reaching that marker.
        driveRequirements - The subsystems that the path following commands should require. Usually just a Drive subsystem.

        Create an auto builder that will create command groups that will handle path following and triggering events.

        This auto builder will use PPRamseteCommand to follow paths.

        Parameters:
        poseSupplier - A function that supplies the robot pose - use one of the odometry classes to provide this.
        resetPose - A consumer that accepts a Pose2d to reset robot odometry. This will typically be called once at the beginning of an auto.

        driveConstants - PIDConstants for each side of the drive train
        outputVolts - Output consumer that accepts left and right voltages
        eventMap - Map of event marker names to the commands that should run when reaching that marker.
        useAllianceColor - Should the path states be automatically transformed based on alliance color? In order for this to work properly, you MUST create your path on the blue side of the field.
        driveRequirements - The subsystems that the path following commands should require. Usually just a Drive subsystem.

      • followPath

        public CommandBase followPath​(PathPlannerTrajectory trajectory)
        Description copied from class: BaseAutoBuilder
        Create a path following command for a given trajectory. This will not trigger any events while path following.

        Override this to create auto builders for your custom path following commands.

        Specified by:
        followPath in class BaseAutoBuilder
        Parameters:
        trajectory - The trajectory to follow
        Returns:
        A path following command for the given trajectory
